%N A179562 Number of permutations of [n] with the number moved left exceeding the number moved right by 1.
%H A179562 Seiichi Manyama, <a href="/A179562/b179562.txt">Table of n, a(n) for n = 1..450</a>
%F A179562 a(n) = Sum_{e=0..floor((n+1)/2)} binomial(n,2*e-1) * A271697(2*e-1,e). - _Seiichi Manyama_, Apr 23 2026
%o A179562 (PARI) E(n, k) = sum(j=0, k, (-1)^j*binomial(n+1, j)*(k+1-j)^n);
%o A179562 a271697(n, k) = sum(j=0, n, (-1)^(n-j)*binomial(n, j)*E(j, k));
%o A179562 a(n) = sum(e=0, (n+1)\2, binomial(n, 2*e-1)*a271697(2*e-1, e)); \\ _Seiichi Manyama_, Apr 23 2026
